HEADWORD: Æthrioscope
<hw>⟦AE⟧"thri*o*scope</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
clear + <?/ to observe.]</ety> <def>An instrument consisting in part of
a differential thermometer. It is used for measuring changes of
temperature produced by different conditions of the sky, as when clear
or clouded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

